         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Wedinos Laboratory Equipment</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>17/2387/EC</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="38433000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The NHS Wales Shared Services Partnership, hosted by Velindre NHS Trust are acting on behalf of Cardiff and Vale University Local Health Board who are seeking to establish a contract for the capital purchase of a Mass Spectrometer and uHPLC and a FT-IR Spectroscopy and associated maintenance.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <LOT_DIVISION>
               <LOT_ALL/>
            </LOT_DIVISION>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>FT-IR Spectroscopy</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>2</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="38000000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="38433000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKL22"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>To compliment Lot 2, a fourier-transform infrared (FT-IR) spectrometer is required for the identification of drugs plus excipients.</P>
                  <P>The instrument should:</P>
                  <P>— be portable but robust for use outside of the laboratory,</P>
                  <P>— be able to analyse samples including powders and tablets directly or with minimum pretreatment,</P>
                  <P>— contain all the hardware required for this,</P>
                  <P>— come with a library of compounds to aid identification.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">36</DURATION>
               <NO_RENEWAL/>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="2">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Mass Spectrometer and uHPLC</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>1</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="38000000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="38433100"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKL22"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Toxicology Laboratories located at the University Hospital Llandough require a high-resolution mass-spectrometer capable of measuring exact mass on precursor and fragment ions for the purpose of identifying psychoactive drugs, steroids and other peptides for the WEDINOS project. The instrument must:</P>
                  <P>— be provided with a solution for presenting samples of powders, tablets and plant material (that may be dissolved in solvents) to the mass spectrometer for analysis, which must include a suitable uHPLC system,</P>
                  <P>— be capable of analysing small molecules and large intact proteins with masses of at least 35 kDa,</P>
                  <P>— be capable of generating fragment ions for matching the sample to library compounds.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">36</DURATION>
               <NO_RENEWAL/>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
